Q2.What are the features of Spring Framework?

Ans = Features:
1. IoC Container
During runtime, an object needs to be referenced implicitly and the task is taken up by IoC container. This container consists of
assembler code that takes care of configuration management. 

2. Data Access Framework
This feature enables the developer to use persistence APIs. For storing persistence data in the database using JDBC.

3. Spring MVC Framework
This framework feature helps developers in building web applications on the basis of MVC architecture.

4. Transaction Management
As the name suggests this framework helps in building a transaction management system without intervening with the code. 

5. JDBC Abstraction Layer
This feature helps the developer in handling errors in an easy and efficient manner. The abstraction layer here helps in reducing
the JDBC programming code.








